   3.586862209475972*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3edca851-9f9a-472c-a637-\
09d80667823d"],

Cell["\<\
NDiagonalize may be used to convert any superoperator into a form which is \
diagonalized in a specified operator basis (or in the current operator basis, \
by default). The output of NDiagonalize is a special form of Superoperator \
which may be used just like any other superoperator. Certain routines run \
faster when superoperators have been preconverted into a diagonalized form. \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.586862213480266*^9, 3.586862265428812*^9}, {
  3.58686231998557*^9, 3.586862390470214*^9}, {3.5868627775022497`*^9, 
  3.586862807892778*^9}, {3.5868629988149967`*^9, 
  3.586863021765124*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3c879134-3c42-4bd6-b366-\
2eb159c906ea"],

